@deffn sinc (x)
Return the normalized sinc function. Explicitly, this function is defined as
@displaymath
sinc(x) = sin(x)/x   for x != 0
sinc(0) = 1
@end displaymath

@displaymath
sinc(x) = sin(x)/x   (x != 0)
sinc(0) = 1
@end displaymath

For nonzero @var{x}, @code{sinc(x)} evaluates to @code{sin(x)/x}.
At @code{x = 0} the value is defined to be @code{1}.

@example
(%i1) sinc(%pi/3);
...
@end example

@itemize @bullet
@item
@samp{sinc(x)} is an even function.

@item
The singularity at @code{x = 0} is removable.

@item
Symbolic simplification rewrites @code{sinc(x)} to @code{sin(x)/x}
when @code{x != 0}.
@end itemize

@end deffn